2026-03-11 03:44:42,725 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"tools": [{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_read_file", "description": "Read a ticket or document from the project board (data/project_board/).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_write_file", "description": "Create or update a ticket/document on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "content", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path", "content"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_create_directory", "description": "Create a directory on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_list_directory", "description": "List entries on the project board.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"default": "", "description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_get_file_info", "description": "Get metadata for a board path.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "board_read_multiple_files", "description": "Read multiple board files at once.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"paths": {"description": "paths", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Paths", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["paths"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_read_file", "description": "Read a knowledge-base document (data/knowledge_base/).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_write_file", "description": "Create or update a knowledge-base document.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "content", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path", "content"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_create_directory", "description": "Create a directory in the knowledge base.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_list_directory", "description": "List entries in the knowledge base.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"default": "", "description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_get_file_info", "description": "Get metadata for a knowledge-base path.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_read_multiple_files", "description": "Read multiple knowledge-base files at once.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"paths": {"description": "paths", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Paths", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["paths"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Alice, a seasoned Project Manager.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Understand the user's idea or requirement thoroughly.\n- Break the work into clear, actionable tasks for the rest of the team\n  (Architect, Engineer, CodeReviewer, QA).\n- Delegate each task to the appropriate specialist and wait for their\n  result before deciding the next step.\n- Synthesise all specialist results into a coherent final summary\n  when the project is complete.\n- For each user request, create one or more tickets on the project board\n  (data/project_board/) that capture the requirement and track status.\n- Maintain a simple Kanban-style workflow on the board with statuses:\n  TO DO, IN PROGRESS, IN REVIEW, DONE.\n- Ensure that ticket statuses reflect reality as work progresses, and that\n  tickets link to any relevant knowledge base docs and code locations.\n- Together with the Architect, document the agreed approach and design for\n  each user request in the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*  : read and inspect files in the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*   : read documentation and knowledge base files (data/knowledge_base/).\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT write or modify code directly.\n- When creating or updating tickets, include at least: a short title, a\n  description, current Status (one of TO DO, IN PROGRESS, IN REVIEW, DONE),\n  and any links to design docs or code paths.\n- You may update ticket status yourself, and other roles may also update\n  the status as they start or finish work on a ticket.\n- Always confirm a specialist has finished before delegating the next task.\n- When all tasks are complete, respond with a final summary that begins\n  with the exact text: \"PROJECT COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_vfuvf2xSghBGWjfPmDrrO3J5", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_CBFTcR3GFfNidaJXbhtaOfAS", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api\"}", "name": "docs_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": "To create a REST API for a todo app, we need to break down the project into several tasks and delegate them to the relevant team members. Here's the initial breakdown:\n\n1. **Design the API structure and endpoints**: This includes determining what resources the API needs to handle (e.g., tasks, lists, users) and what endpoints will be required for CRUD operations.\n\n2. **Define database schema**: Identify the data model and relationships that the API needs to support.\n\n3. **Implement the API**: Handling requests, responses, validations, and error-handling logic.\n\n4. **Code Review**: Ensure that the API implementation meets coding standards and works as expected.\n\n5. **Testing the API**: Verify that the API functions correctly through unit tests, integration tests, and other quality assurance methods.\n\n6. **Documentation**: Document the API's endpoints, usage, and any relevant information for developers.\n\nLet's start by creating tickets for these tasks on the project board."}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_app_api", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_vfuvf2xSghBGWjfPmDrrO3J5"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_CBFTcR3GFfNidaJXbhtaOfAS"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "# Todo App API Requirements\n\n## Features\n1. **Create a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\n\n2. **Read Todos**\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\n\n3. **Update a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\n\n4. **Delete a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\n\n5. **Authentication**\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\n\n6. **User Management**\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n1. **Scalability**\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\n\n2. **Maintainability**\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Security**\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\n4. **Performance**\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load."}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DHyEOKxGMBYRHXvZulDh9iGuKvkTk", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "Let's proceed with creating the tickets for each of the tasks defined in the project. I'll include the requirements link in the respective tickets.\n\n### Tickets to be created:\n1. **Design API Structure and Endpoints**\n2. **Define Database Schema**\n3. **Implement API**\n4. **Code Review**\n5. **Testing the API**\n6. **Documentation**\n\nI will now create and update these tickets on the project board.", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_DKI8LuqOk9QEqFw4T5faJaaE", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\", \"content\": \"# Design API Structure and Endpoints\\n\\n## Description\\nDesign the structure and endpoints for the todo app API. Determine the necessary resources (e.g., tasks, lists, users) and define the CRUD operations required.\\n\\n## Status\\nTO DO\\n\\n## Links\\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_dCxGnLfJTrtzAG254R0xlro5", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/2_define_database_schema.md\", \"content\": \"# Define Database Schema\\n\\n## Description\\nOutline the data model and relationships that the API needs to support.\\n\\n## Status\\nTO DO\\n\\n## Links\\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_Ji0LoSDCOT8ngaLOThbedcKA", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/3_implement_api.md\", \"content\": \"# Implement the API\\n\\n## Description\\nDevelop the API to handle requests, responses, validations, and error-handling logic based on the design specifications.\\n\\n## Status\\nTO DO\\n\\n## Links\\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_W4gs4C1g15kXd6H1oqkHTgoL", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/4_code_review.md\", \"content\": \"# Code Review\\n\\n## Description\\nReview the API implementation to ensure that it meets coding standards and functions as expected.\\n\\n## Status\\nTO DO\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_1HQUobBlA1MqS0Paiaf7zprW", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/5_testing_the_api.md\", \"content\": \"# Testing the API\\n\\n## Description\\nConduct unit tests, integration tests, and other QA methods to verify the API's functionality.\\n\\n## Status\\nTO DO\\n\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_4wVaRowyRTb1c3H12CZJxPjG", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_app_api/6_document