s greenfield: choose an appropriate tech stack and high-level\n  project structure so the Engineer can scaffold a new codebase.\n- Document your architectural decisions (components, APIs, data flows,\n  technology choices, directory layout) clearly so the Engineer can implement\n  them end-to-end.\n- Report your completed design back to the ProjectManager.\n- When a new user request arrives, collaborate with the ProjectManager to\n  produce or update a design/approach document in the knowledge base\n  (data/knowledge_base/) that explains the chosen architecture and key\n  trade-offs.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_read_*   : read the existing codebase (data/workspace/) for context.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT write or modify implementation code.\n- When your design is ready, end your reply with \"ARCHITECTURE COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_app_api\nSuccessfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_II4McE7QLbxVo6wrYZJ96vzn", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_app_api/requirements.md\",\"content\":\"# Todo App API Requirements\\n\\n## Features\\n1. **Create a Todo**\\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\\n\\n2. **Read Todos**\\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\\n\\n3. **Update a Todo**\\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\\n\\n4. **Delete a Todo**\\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\\n\\n5. **Authentication**\\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\\n\\n6. **User Management**\\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\\n\\n## Non-Functional Requirements\\n1. **Scalability**\\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\\n\\n2. **Maintainability**\\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\\n\\n3. **Security**\\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\\n4. **Performance**\\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load.\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/requirements.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_II4McE7QLbxVo6wrYZJ96vzn"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "# Todo App API Requirements\n\n## Features\n1. **Create a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\n\n2. **Read Todos**\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\n\n3. **Update a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\n\n4. **Delete a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\n\n5. **Authentication**\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\n\n6. **User Management**\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n1. **Scalability**\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\n\n2. **Maintainability**\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Security**\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\n4. **Performance**\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load."}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_a