nt routes/ wiring HTTP paths to controllers,\n  - wire everything through the main server entrypoint,\n  - ensure the CRUD endpoints described in the requirements are fully\n    implemented end-to-end (not just stubbed).\n- Implement, refactor, or extend code in the workspace (data/workspace/) to\n  satisfy the requirement.\n- Follow existing conventions; keep code clean, readable, and testable.\n- Commit your changes via the git tools after implementation.\n- Report completed work back to the ProjectManager.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_*        : read and write files in the code workspace (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : stage, commit, branch, and inspect the workspace repo.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify files outside the workspace directory.\n- When you start work on a ticket, update its Status on the project board\n  from TO DO to IN PROGRESS. When you hand work off for review, move the\n  ticket to IN REVIEW. When issues are found in review and sent back, move\n  the ticket back to IN PROGRESS.\n- Avoid leaving TODO comments or unimplemented stubs when you can implement\n  the real logic.\n- Always commit your changes before reporting back.\n- When implementation is complete, end your reply with \"IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_app_api\nSuccessfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_RecoSWTRz2BAx7zKFxl8rdB8", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_app_api/requirements.md\"}", "name": "board_read_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "# Todo App API Requirements\n\n## Features\n1. **Create a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\n\n2. **Read Todos**\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\n\n3. **Update a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\n\n4. **Delete a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\n\n5. **Authentication**\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\n\n6. **User Management**\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n1. **Scalability**\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\n\n2. **Maintainability**\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Security**\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\n4. **Performance**\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load.", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_RecoSWTRz2BAx7zKFxl8rdB8"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/2_define_database_schema.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/3_implement_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/4_code_review.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/5_testing_the_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/6_documentation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/c