- Following the database schema, the **Engineer** will develop the API.\n\n4. **Code Review**:\n    - After implementation, the **CodeReviewer** will assess the code quality and functionality.\n\n5. **Testing the API**:\n    - The **QA** specialist will ensure the API's reliability through thorough testing.\n    \n6. **Documentation**:\n    - Finally, the **Architect** or designated team member will document the API for developers.\n\nPlease let me know when you're ready to begin or if there are any questions or additional requirements!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "# Design API Structure and Endpoints\n\n## Description\nDesign the structure and endpoints for the todo app API. Determine the necessary resources (e.g., tasks, lists, users) and define the CRUD operations required.\n\n## Status\nTO DO\n\n## Links\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DHyElAwawA1bStYuCi8fbMGR9bVrd", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "The initial project planning and setup have been completed. The requirements for the Todo App API are documented, and tasks have been outlined for the project's implementation. The next step is for each specialist to begin working on their respective tasks according to the project board.\n\nThe requirements document has been successfully stored in the knowledge base. Please proceed with task assignments and execution based on your roles.\n\nIf there are any specific questions or if additional information is required, feel free to reach out.\n\nREVIEW COMPLETE", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null}}], "created": 1773175499, "model": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "