read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- code_read_*   : read the implementation code (data/workspace/).\n- browser_*     : drive a headless browser via Playwright for UI checks.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify implementation code.\n- When you finish validating a ticket, add a brief summary of the test\n  results to the ticket on the project board and/or an appropriate document\n  in the knowledge base, and make sure the ticket Status accurately reflects\n  whether the work is DONE or needs further changes.\n- When all testing is complete, end your reply with \"QA COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_app_api\nSuccessfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "# Todo App API Requirements\n\n## Features\n1. **Create a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\n\n2. **Read Todos**\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\n\n3. **Update a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\n\n4. **Delete a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\n\n5. **Authentication**\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\n\n6. **User Management**\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n1. **Scalability**\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\n\n2. **Maintainability**\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Security**\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\n4. **Performance**\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load."}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_8ZcOLIX482fBFCCJInUrDhRF", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"project_board/todo_app_api\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_8ZcOLIX482fBFCCJInUrDhRF"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/2_define_database_schema.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/3_implement_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/4_code_review.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/5_testing_the_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/6_documentation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_app_api'"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "[FILE] 1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\n[FILE] 2_define_database_schema.md\n[FILE] 3_implement_api.md\n[FILE] 4_code_review.md\n[FILE] 5_testing_the_api.md\n[FILE] 6_documentation.md\n[FILE] requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/knowledge_base/data/project_board/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_tBBrecMJiblcsuXPnAsSeCR0", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"project_board/todo_app_api/5_testing_the_api.md\"}", "name": "board_read_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cer