nt routes/ wiring HTTP paths to controllers,\n  - wire everything through the main server entrypoint,\n  - ensure the CRUD endpoints described in the requirements are fully\n    implemented end-to-end (not just stubbed).\n- Implement, refactor, or extend code in the workspace (data/workspace/) to\n  satisfy the requirement.\n- Follow existing conventions; keep code clean, readable, and testable.\n- Commit your changes via the git tools after implementation.\n- Report completed work back to the ProjectManager.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_*        : read and write files in the code workspace (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : stage, commit, branch, and inspect the workspace repo.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify files outside the workspace directory.\n- When you start work on a ticket, update its Status on the project board\n  from TO DO to IN PROGRESS. When you hand work off for review, move the\n  ticket to IN REVIEW. When issues are found in review and sent back, move\n  the ticket back to IN PROGRESS.\n- Avoid leaving TODO comments or unimplemented stubs when you can implement\n  the real logic.\n- Always commit your changes before reporting back.\n- When implementation is complete, end your reply with \"IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_app_api\nSuccessfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_RecoSWTRz2BAx7zKFxl8rdB8", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_app_api/requirements.md\"}", "name": "board_read_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "# Todo App API Requirements\n\n## Features\n1. **Create a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to create a new todo item with details such as title, description, due date, and status.\n\n2. **Read Todos**\n   - Endpoint to retrieve all todo items or filter them by status or due date.\n\n3. **Update a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to update details of an existing todo item.\n\n4. **Delete a Todo**\n   - Endpoint to delete a todo item.\n\n5. **Authentication**\n   - Use JWT for user authentication.\n\n6. **User Management**\n   - Endpoints for user registration and login.\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n1. **Scalability**\n   - Design should support scaling horizontally.\n\n2. **Maintainability**\n   - Codebase should be modular and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Security**\n   - Ensure data protection through authentication and authorization.\n4. **Performance**\n   - API should respond within 200ms under normal load.", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_RecoSWTRz2BAx7zKFxl8rdB8"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/2_define_database_schema.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/3_implement_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/4_code_review.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/5_testing_the_api.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/6_documentation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_app_api'"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_nuqDsNwifK7r7OCnIZXUGsL0", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_app_api\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[FILE] 1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\n[FILE] 2_define_database_schema.md\n[FILE] 3_implement_api.md\n[FILE] 4_code_review.md\n[FILE] 5_testing_the_api.md\n[FILE] 6_documentation.md\n[FILE] requirements.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_nuqDsNwifK7r7OCnIZXUGsL0"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/knowledge_base/data/project_board/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "All tasks have been broken down and documented in the project board. The next step is for specialists to begin working on the tickets. Here's a quick overview of what needs to be done for each:\n\n1. **Design API Structure and Endpoints**: \n    - **Architect**, please take this task and design the appropriate endpoints and structure needed for the todo app API.\n\n2. **Define Database Schema**:\n    - Once the design is ready, the **Architect** will also define the data model and relationships.\n\n3. **Implement API**:\n    - Following the database schema, the **Engineer** will develop the API.\n\n4. **Code Review**:\n    - After implementation, the **CodeReviewer** will assess the code quality and functionality.\n\n5. **Testing the API**:\n    - The **QA** specialist will ensure the API's reliability through thorough testing.\n    \n6. **Documentation**:\n    - Finally, the **Architect** or designated team member will document the API for developers.\n\nPlease let me know when you're ready to begin or if there are any questions or additional requirements!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "# Design API Structure and Endpoints\n\n## Description\nDesign the structure and endpoints for the todo app API. Determine the necessary resources (e.g., tasks, lists, users) and define the CRUD operations required.\n\n## Status\nTO DO\n\n## Links\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_yDnPLxXQkQ6xwmvYjYjfxP2B", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md\",\"content\":\"# Design API Structure and Endpoints\\n\\n## Description\\nDesign the structure and endpoints for the todo app API. Determine the necessary resources (e.g., tasks, lists, users) and define the CRUD operations required.\\n\\n## Status\\nIN PROGRESS\\n\\n## Links\\n- [Requirements](data/knowledge_base/todo_app_api/requirements.md)\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_app_api/1_design_api_structure_and_endpoints.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_yDnPLxXQkQ6xwmvYjYjfxP2B"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "The initial project planning and setup have been completed. The requirements for the Todo App API are documented, and tasks have been outlined for the project's implementation. The next step is for each specialist to begin working on their respective tasks according to the project board.\n\nThe requirements document has been successfully stored in the knowledge base. Please proceed with task assignments and execution based on your roles.\n\nIf there are any specific questions or if additional information is required, feel free to reach out.\n\nREVIEW COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/project_board/todo_app_api"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "The project setup for the Todo App API is ready, and tasks have been documented on the project board. Each specialist can now begin their respective tasks. Here's the current status:\n\n1. **Design API Structure and Endpoints**: Ready for the Architect to start.\n2. **Define Database Schema**: Will proceed once the design is complete.\n3. **Implement API**: Awaits database schema definition.\n4. **Code Review**: To follow the implementation.\n5. **Testing the API**: To commence after code review.\n6. **Documentation**: To be finalized after testing.\n\nPlease let me know if you have any questions or if further actions are needed!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "To design a REST API for the Todo application, we will focus on creating a modular, scalable, and maintainable architecture that addresses the needs outlined in the requirements.\n\n## Architectural Design\n\n### Technology Stack\n- **Backend Framework:** Node.js with Express.js\n- **Database:** MongoDB with Mongoose ODM\n- **Authentication:** JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for user authentication\n- **Version Control:** Git\n- **Deployment:** Docker for containerization, Kubernetes for orchestration\n\n### Directory Structure\n1. **controllers/** - Define the logic for processing requests and interacting with models.\n   - `todoController.js` - Handles todo-related endpoints.\n   - `userController.js` - Handles user-related endpoints.\n   \n2. **models/** - Define Mongoose schemas and models.\n   - `todoModel.js` - Schema for todo items.\n   - `userModel.js` - Schema for users.\n   \n3. **routes/** - Define the API routes.\n   - `todoRoutes.js` - Routes for todo operations.\n   - `userRoutes.js` - Routes for user operations.\n   \n4. **middleware/** - Custom middleware for authentication and validation.\n   - `authMiddleware.js` - Middleware for JWT verification.\n   \n5. **utils/** - Utility functions such as error handling and response formatting.\n6. **config/** - Configuration files for database and environment variables.\n   - `dbConfig.js` - MongoDB connection configuration.\n   - `default.json` - Default configuration file for environment-specific settings.\n   \n7. **tests/** - Unit and integration tests.\n8. **.env** - Environment variables.\n9. **Dockerfile** - Docker configuration for containerizing the application.\n10. **docker-compose.yml** - Setup for Docker services.\n11. **README.md** - Project documentation.\n\n### API Endpoints\n1. **Todo Endpoints**\n   - `POST /todos` - Create a new todo item.\n   - `GET /todos` - Retrieve all todo items or filter by status and due date.\n   - `GET /todos/:id` - Retrieve a specific todo item by ID.\n   - `PUT /todos/:id` - Update a specific todo item.\n   - `DELETE /todos/:id` - Delete a specific todo item.\n\n2. **User Endpoints**\n   - `POST /users/register` - Register a new user.\n   - `POST /users/login` - User login.\n\n### Security\n- Use HTTPS for secure data transmission.\n- Store sensitive information like database credentials and JWT secrets in environment variables.\n- Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse.\n\n### Scalability\n- Design the application to be stateless, allowing multiple instances to run concurrently.\n- Use a load balancer to distribute incoming requests across instances.\n\n### Testing\n- Use Jest and Supertest for unit and integration testing.\n- Set up continuous integration to run tests on each commit.\n\nThis architecture provides a robust foundation for building a scalable, secure, and maintainable Todo app API. Each module is separated to ensure a clean codebase and facilitate easier updates and maintenance.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DHyF2pF8aRKuv1M0sGFtk3nlaJ53r", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_T8sqGqMcw1DJ6ItN1ph9VFQY", "function": {